Sentencas: A porous nickel-8 mol% yttria stabilized zirconia (Ni-8YSZ) composite, used as anode for solid oxide fuel cell, was obtained by reduction of NiO-8YSZ cermet.
Titulo: Reduction kinetics of NiO-YSZ composite for application in solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The first goal was the evaluation of the temperature effect of powder processing by thermogravimetry.
Titulo: Reduction kinetics of NiO-YSZ composite for application in solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In addition, the influence of porosity in the reduction kinetic of the sample sintered at 1450 A degrees C was evaluated.
Titulo: Reduction kinetics of NiO-YSZ composite for application in solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The final porosity produced in NiO-8YSZ composite by pore former was 30.4 and 37.9 vol.%, respectively, for 10 and 15 mass% of corn starch.
Titulo: Reduction kinetics of NiO-YSZ composite for application in solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The sample with 15 mass% of corn starch promotes a reduction rate almost twice higher than sample with 10 mass% of corn starch.
Titulo: Reduction kinetics of NiO-YSZ composite for application in solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The porosity introduced by the reduction of NiO was 23 vol.%.
Titulo: Reduction kinetics of NiO-YSZ composite for application in solid oxide fuel cell
